# Single kickoff trigger for the JAR2-68 workflow-driven smoke. Without
# this the workflow's first tick drains an empty trigger queue and
# `decide_next_action` sends the LLM a zero-length user message, which
# vendors (Cohere observed; Anthropic likely the same) reject with HTTP
# 400. Mirrors `examples/smoke_llm_mcp/triggers.jsonl`'s shape.
{"delay_ms": 0, "trigger": {"type": "external", "kind": "kickoff", "payload": {}}}
